<HEADLINE> DPR Korea to Send 50-member Delegation to Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's Republic
of Korea will send a 50-member delegation to the upcoming Olympic
Games, Han In Gun, head of the delegation disclosed here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The entourage, including 24 athletes, will compete in boxing,
weightlifting, judo, marathon, table tennis, shooting, diving,
gymnastics and wrestling.
</P>
<P>
Han said the title hopefuls are boxer Ri Chol in the 54kg
class, Pae Gil Su in pommel horse, weightlifter Kim Myong Nam in
70kg category and peddlar Li Gun Sang. 
</P>
