<HEADLINE> Ferreira Nips Gaudenzi in Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WIMBLEDON, ENGLAND, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Wayne Ferreira of South
Africa advanced into the third round of Wimbledon with a
straight-set victory over "bad boy" Andrea Gaudenzi of Italy on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The eleventh seed beat Gaudenzi 7-5, 7-5, 6-4, setting up a
third-round clash against Magnus Gustafsson of Sweden, who earlier
eliminated Australian Todd Woodbridge 7-6 (7-5), 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Gaudenzi got fined 1,000 pounds (1,500 US dollars) for his
unsportsman behavior during his first-round victory over American
Michael Joyce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
