<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Birth Rate Lowered By Abortions, Miscarriages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- As many as 120,000 Bulgarian women
had abortions or miscarriages between January and May, up almost
one-fifth over the whole of last year and leaving the population
growth rate under 0.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, during the first five months of this year, a total of
60,000 babies were born, compared with 79,000 babies in the whole
of 1995, the Trud newspaper reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The increase in abortions has been attributed to the soaring
cost of living and increasing numbers of pregnancies among
unmarried women.
</P>
<P>
The cost of having an abortion in Bulgaria is also surging,
said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
