<HEADLINE> Hekmatyar Assumes Afghan Premiership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Gulbuddin Hekmatyar, leader of
the Afghan Hezb-i-Islami, was sworn in as Afghan prime minister
this evening in the Presidential Palace in Kabul.
</P>
<P>
According to Radio Kabul monitored here, Hekmatyar will now
lead a coalition government of his own faction of the
Hezb-i-Islami and President Burhanuddin Rabbani's Jamiat-i-Islami.
</P>
<P>
Hekmatyar entered the capital by road later this afternoon at
the head of a 100-vehicle convoy despite heavy shelling and rocket
attacks by the Taliban religious student militia.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed between Hekmatyar and Afghan
President Burhanuddin Rabbani last month, Hekmatyar's party will
also be offered key portfolios of defense and finance.  
</P>
</TEXT>
