<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Wednesday
that China and Spain approach the next century with relations that
are healthy and harmonious, thanks to the joint efforts of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- A statement released by the U.S. Embassy in
Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, Wednesday confirmed that so far 17 Americans
had been killed and over 230 others injured in the blast Tuesday
night at a U.S. military compound in the eastern Saudi city of
Dhahran.
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- France has bought hundreds of metric tons of
uranium from South Africa each year since 1977, a local daily "The
Citizen" reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Outgoing South African Mineral and Energy Affairs Minister Pik
Botha disclosed the uranium deal with France in a written response
to questions by senior African National Congress member Willie
Hoffmeyer, the report said.
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia and Iraq have begun talks to explore the
possibility of Iraqi oil exports in exchange for food imports from
Indonesia, Industry and Trade Minister Tunky Ariwibowo said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Spacecraft Galileo will close in on Jupiter's
biggest moon Ganymede early Thursday morning to gather the most
detailed information ever obtained about the icy satellite,
according to a NASA report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
