<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Israeli Soldiers Killed in Jordanian Valley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Three Israeli soldiers were
killed and two others wounded today in an ambush by terrorists
near the Israeli-Jordanian border in Jordanian Valley, Israel
Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The ambush took place early this morning near the Na'aran
settlements several kilometers north of the West Bank city of
Jericho, when an Israeli border patrol came under sudden attacks
by three to five armed terrorists, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The attackers, believed to have crossed the Jordanian River
from Jordan, exchanged fires with the Israeli soldiers for a
short while before fleeing back to Jordan with several guns
snatched from the dead soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The two wounded soldiers were evacuated by an Israeli
helicopter to Jerusalem's Hadasha Hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Israeli army contacted the Jordanian border troops and
conducted joint search for the terrorists.
</P>
<P>
So far no one has claimed responsibility for the
attack. However, Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai blamed
the Jordanian army for failing to prevent the infiltration,
although acknowledging they have been trying the best to do so.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu sent condolences to
the families of the victims, promising them that Israel will
upgrade cooperation with Jordan in cracking down the terrorists.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian King Hussein telephoned Netanyahu to express his
regret about this attack, pledging Jordan will boost its
efforts to check the armed infiltration to prevent future
attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
