<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Sino-U.S. relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here today that maintaining healthy and stable
relations between China and the U.S. has great significance on
peace, stability and prosperity in the Asian-Pacific region and
the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Spanish newspaper El Pais (The
Country) this morning, Jiang said this is because China and the
U.S. are big countries and permenent members of the UN Security
Council.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is on a four-day state visit to Spain at the invitation
of King Juan Carlos I.
</P>
<P>
"I proposed, as early as in 1992, that China and the U.S.
should increase trust, reduce troubles, develop cooperation and
avert confrontation," Jiang said during the interview.
</P>
<P>
"This remains to be our basic policy in handling Sino-U.S.
relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
The key to healthy and stable Sino-U.S. relations is adherence
to the principles enthroned in the three Sino-U.S. joint
communiques, especially the principles of mutual respect for
sovereignty and territorial integrity and non-interference in each
other's internal affairs, the proper handling of the Taiwan issue,
and the proper handling of every single problem in bilateral
relations in the spirit of mutual respect and consultation on
equal footing, Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he has taken notice of some positive signals with
regard to Sino-U.S. relations made by U.S. leaders recently.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that as long as both sides give priority to the
fundamental interests of the two countries and the two peoples,
treat and tackle bilateral relations from a strategic height and
long-term perspective, China and the U.S. can overcome differences
and frictions and put bilateral relations on track of normal and
healthy development," Jiang emphasized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
