<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Says China not to Privatize State-owned Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today that China will not privatize its state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Concerning the ownership system, China will keep public
ownership system as the mainstay of the economy while letting
diversified economic elements to develop concurrently, Jiang said
in an interview with El Pais, the most influential newspaper in
Spain.
</P>
<P>
"Private ownership economy is but a necessary supplement to the
socialist economy," he underlined.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in Madrid on Monday for a four-day state visit to
Spain with the purpose of strengthening political and economic
ties with this southern European country.
</P>
<P>
The president said China's reform and opening-up are aimed at
building socialism with Chinese characteristics and developing
socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Talking about China's economic policies, Jiang said opening up
and reform are a basic policy of China, which has already achieved
remarkable results.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, China's accumulated import and export
rose to more than 1 trillion U.S. dollars, he said, adding China
will open wider to the rest of the world and make full use of
domestic and foreign resources and markets.
</P>
<P>
"We will gradually open the sectors of finance, business,
tourism and services, to meet the demand of reform and
development," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also emphasized that the central government will use
economic, legal and necessary administrative levers to strengthen
macro-control over the national economy to ensure its rapid and
healthy development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
