<HEADLINE> UN Council Condemns Terrorist Attacks on US Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security Council
on Wednesday condemned the terrorist attack on a U.S. airforce
base in Dhahran, Saudi Arabia, that killed 16 Americans and
wounding 64 others.
</P>
<P>
In an oral statement to the press, Council President Nabil A.
Elaraby said that the council have reemphasized their strong
condemnation of all acts of terror and considered them "alien to
the moral and the spiritual values shared by the people of the
world."
</P>
<P>
The council members "reaffirmed their intention to stand
staunchly against all such acts," Elaraby said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said the council members had expressed their
condolences to the families of the victims in the tragic
explosion, to the government of Saudi Arabia, to the government of
the United States and other countries whose nationals were victims
of the explosion.  
</P>
