<HEADLINE> Ghali Confers in Britain on His Second Term Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- U.N Secretary-General Boutros
Boutros-Ghali discussed his second term bid with British Foreign
Secretary Malcolm Rifkind today immediately after his talk with
British Prime minister John Major last night.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Ghali's second term bid, their talks focused on a
range of U.N affairs, such as U.N reform and U.N finances. They
also discussed what happens in Bosnia after the departure of U.N
peace-keeping forces, as well as Burundi, Nigeria and Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The British Government did not issued any formal statement on
the talks. However, an official from Foreign Office gave this
reporter a brief account of their talks in a telephon-interview.
</P>
