had served U.N with honour in one of the world's most difficult
assignments.
</P>
<P>
On the question of Britain's attitude towards Ghali's second
term bid, the official said "Britain does not comment publicly on
the election of the Secretary-General. As for Mr Ghali, there are
still 6 months to run and a full agenda ahead."
</P>
<P>
He also said: "Before consultations with its allies, Britain
will not make decision on the U.N post."
</P>
<P>
diplomats here said leaders from the seven industrial nations
will consult privately on Ghali's bid in the coming summit in
Lyon, France.  
