<HEADLINE> Chirac Calls for Unified Efforts in Fighting Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- French president Jacques Chirac
Wednesday called for a unified effort by Western countries and
their allies in the Gulf region in fighting terrorism.
</P>
<P>
In his messages sent to U.S. president Bill Clinton and King
Fahd of Saudi Arabia after the bloody explosion at an air base in
Khobar near Dahran, eastern Saudi Arabia, Chirac expressed his
"sad condolences" and asked the two heads of state to deliver
them to the families of the victims in the explosion.
</P>
<P>
