<HEADLINE> Davenport Exits in Wimbledon Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WIMBLEDON, ENGLAND, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Eighth seed Lindsay
Davenport of the United States joined the exodus of seeds in
Wimbledon when she lost to Larisa Neiland of Latvia in the second
round on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, a quarter-finalist here two years ago, was
apparently not in form and made a string of errors, dropping the
match 6-3, 6-2 within less than one hour.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old unseeded Latvian's best feat was a Wimbledon
doubles title when she was paired with Natalia Zvereva in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Former Wimbledon runner-up and sixth seed Jana Novotna of Czech
Republic also advanced into the third round with a straight-set
7-6 (7-4), 6-3 win over Belgium's Laurence Courtois.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's 15-year-old rising star Martina Hingis, seeded
16th, needed only 40 minutes to win 6-1, 6-1 against Briton Rachel
Viollet, a wild card entry now living in Florida.
</P>
<P>
Hingis's compatriot Marc Rosset, the men's 14th seed, beat
Russian Andrei Olhovsky 6-3, 7-6, 6-4 in the second round and
Dutchman Richard Krajicek, who came in as 17th seed after number
seven Thomas Muster withdrew from the draw, defeated American
Derrick Rostagno 6-4, 6-3, 6-3. 
</P>
