<HEADLINE> Special Parks for Shanghai's Returned Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- An inaugural ceremony for three
special industrial parks prepared for returned students was held
today in Shanghai, the largest metropolitan business center of
China.
</P>
<P>
The Zhangjiang, Jiading, and Caohejing industrial parks will
be given preferential treatment by the municipal government to
help returning students realize their ambitions, local authorities
explain.
</P>
<P>
Large numbers of workshops, residential buildings, and
telecommunication facilities are taking shape in the parks, they
said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope the returned students will play a larger role in
Shanghai's economic expansion," an official told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that returned students already have a total of 343
enterprises in the municipality, with combined registered capital
of 16.5 million US dollars. 
</P>
