<HEADLINE> Mediterranean Women Conference Opens in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Around 100 women from the
Mediterranean, the Balkans and the Middle East are attending the
fifth annual conference of the Association of Women of the
Mediterranean Region (AWMR), which opened Wednesday night in
Cyprus' southern coastal town Limassol.
</P>
<P>
AWMR President Jana Mintoff Bland said today that the main
themes of the conference are the issues of immigration and
refugees.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the conference is held in
Cyprus. Women from all walks of life and political circles are
taking part in the conference, which will end on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Mintoff Bland noted that 80 percent of refugees is women and
children, adding that the conference "is concerned of their
increasing number".
</P>
<P>
Women from Lebanon, Israel, the Palestinian self-rule areas,
and the territories that used to form former Yugoslavia will put
forward their own experiences resulting from war situations.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the conference, Cyprus'
Justice and Public Order Minister Alecos Evangelou stressed his
government's "sensitivity on matters of peace, human rights and
justice" and its determination to fight for their protection and
restoration.
</P>
<P>
He spoke of "the ratification by Cyprus of the U.N. convention
on the elimination of all forms of discrimination against women
in 1985".
</P>
<P>
The minister said this has "a tremendous impact on further
progress as it has provided the general framework of government
policy in promoting women's issues."
</P>
