<HEADLINE> Washing Machine Manufacturer Offers B Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 27 (Xinhua) -- China's largest washing machine
producer, the Wuxi Little Swan Co. Ltd., will offer 70 million B
shares on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The par value 4.464 Hong Kong dollar shares will be
underwritten by the Shenzhen Dapeng Securities Co. and three
overseas securities institutions.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Stock Exchange has agreed to list the shares,
which are denominated in yuan but quoted in foreign currencies and
restricted to overseas buyers, on July 18.
</P>
<P>
Company executives expect the share issue, coordinated by
Barings Bank, to raise 37.39 million US dollars' worth of
funds. Of that, 19.7 million US dollars will be used to expand
production and 15.7 million US dollars for joint-venture projects
with Japanese and German companies.
</P>
<P>
The new joint ventures will produce 500,000 freon-free
refrigerators, 1.3 million refrigerator compressors, and 200,000
exhaust fans and an equal number of sets of kitchen utensils each
year.
</P>
<P>
Profits at Little Swan have been growing at an annual rate of
40 percent in recent years, according to the company executives.
</P>
<P>
Official data shows that Little Swan's market share at home has
been 40 percent or more for seven consecutive years, with annual
sales of 808,300 units in 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
