<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EC Aids Restructuring of Austria's Textile Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC) said
today that it will provide Austria with 2.6 million ECU (3.44
million U.S. dollars) to modernize the country's textile and
garment industry.
</P>
<P>
The money, from the European Union's Structure Funds, will also
be used to help diversify the economy of predominantly
textile-producing regions such as Lower Austria, Styria and
Vorarlberg.
</P>
<P>
The assistance will go toward the introduction of new
manufacturing technologies and new products, their proper
marketing, the promotion of cooperation schemes between firms and
vocational training measures.
</P>
<P>
The EC's total investment in the program is 16.2 million ECU
(21.06 million dollars), which will be matched by 2.6 million ECU
(3.44 million dollars) from Austria's public funds and 11 million
ECU (14.3 million dollars) from the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The EC said that the program, which will last until the end of
1997, will especially benefit small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
