<HEADLINE> England Wins Fair Play Award at European Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The European soccer governing body
UEFA decided on Thursday to honor the Fair Play Trophy to England
despite its defeat to Germany in the semifinal.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday night, England lost the shout-out 6-5 to Germany
after their 1-1 tie in the 120-minute competition.
</P>
<P>
No matter who wins Sunday's final between Germany and the Czech
Republic, England remained unchallenged at the top of the Fair
Play chart ahead of both Denmark and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch fans would not go home empty-handed after being voted
the winners of the UEFA "crowd assessment" competition.
</P>
<P>
In the 1990 World Cup in Italy, England also won the FIFA Fair
Play award following its semi-final defeat to Germany in a penalty
shoot-out. 
</P>
