<HEADLINE> Bahrain, Zimbabwe Agree to Establish Diplomatic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain and Zimbabwe have agreed
to establish diplomatic relations at ambassadorial level, a report
from the Bahraini capital of Manama said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the Bahraini Foreign
Ministry, this decision came in line with a mutual wish by the two
countries to promote their ties of friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"The two sides are eager to develop these ties on the basis of
mutual respect for each other's sovereignty and territorial
integrity, stressing their adherence to the U.N. principles that
call for maintaining international peace and security," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain is the second Gulf Cooperation Council(GCC) state to
establish diplomatic relations with Zimbabwe in one week, as the
United Arab Emirates forged diplomatic relations with Zimbabwe on
June 24.
</P>
<P>
This move indicates that Zimbabwe is seeking to have ties,
especially economic ones, with the GCC states. The other members
of the GCC are Kuwait, Oman, Qatar and Saudi Arabia.
