<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jobless Rate Rises Slightly in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Italy's unemployment rate stood at
12.3 percent in April, rising by one percentage point from
January, according to figures released today by the central
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
But April's jobless rate was only 0.3 percentage points higher
than in the same period last year, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period in 1995, April's jobless rate in
the north dropped by one percentage point to 6.5 percent, while
that for the south increased by one point to 22.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment was highest among young people, at 34.5 percent,
an increase of 4.4 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate among youth in the south hit 57.3 percent,
more than double that for their counterparts in the north, the
figures showed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960627.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coldest June in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The temperature in Lhasa, the
capital city of the Tibet Autonomous Region, dropped to two
degrees centigrade during the first ten days of June, the lowest
ever recorded during June in the region.
</P>
<P>
According to the local meteorological department, the recorded
lowest temperature in Lhasa's history was 2.3 degrees on June 2,
1959.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said that the average temperature in most
parts of Tibet is more than one degree lower than it was in the
same period previously, and was even four to five degrees lower in
Lhasa and the Nagqu region in northern Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Experts said , the cold rainy weather will not harm most of the
crops, but corn and potatoes may be damaged at some point.
</P>
<P>
From June 9 to 17, temperatures rose and rainfall diminished in
most parts of Tibet. The northern Qamdo and the eastern Nagqu
regions had twice moderate rains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960627.0090 </DOCNO>
