</P>
<P>
-- The "Desert Storm" operation, in which the Americans made
the Saudis pay for its military costs, had consequently made the
Saudi budget red.
</P>
<P>
Taking advantage of the war, the United States has in the
meantime become the number-one arms seller to the (Gulf)
region. In this context, the U.S. presence is being more and more
resented in the region.
</P>
<P>
La Nouvelle Republique du Centre Ouest:
</P>
<P>
-- Western presence in the Gulf region has aroused the
development of an Islamic fundamentalist resistance movement in
the kingdom (Saudi Arabia).
</P>
<P>
La Presse de la Manch:
</P>
<P>
-- Rich countries have mainly created the poor in their own
people in the past few years. Now they will have to fight poverty
beyond their borders.
</P>
<P>
La Montagne
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the G-7 countries should take into account the grave
social fallout of the globalization and make a significant gesture
to help the developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
