<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Unemployment Rate Falls in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine unemployment rate
fell to 10.9 percent in April this year, 1.2 percent down from the
same period last year, the Philippine Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to the National Statistics Office (NSO), the number
of unemployed Filipinos as of last April declined to 3.4 million
from 3.53 million a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The drop in unemployment was mainly due to an increase in the
number of people who work for less than 40 hours a week. Some of
these people look for additional hours of work.
</P>
<P>
However, full-time workers or those who work for at least 40
hours a week fell from 15.8 million to 15.1 million during the
survey period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
