stressed.
</P>
<P>
Talking about the role of banks in the liberalization era, Deve
Gowda said that banks had the responsibility to keep deposits
safely and utilize for selfless service for the country. Poverty
could be wiped out from the face of the country just with the
interest generated from the deposits of banks and financial
institutions in India.  
</P>
