the riots on Thursday triggered off after England lost to Germany
in the semifinal of the European Championship.
</P>
<P>
About 30 others were injuried when some 2,000 fans who prepared
for a celebration in Trafalgar Square were pulled into misery by
England's defeat on penalties.
</P>
<P>
The trouble-makers unleashed their angry by breaking windows,
setting fire to cars and even throwing bottles at riot police.
</P>
<P>
Among the injured, none was seriously hurt, police said.
</P>
<P>
However, a 17-year-old Russian student was stabbed in Portslade
by angry fans who considered him as a German.
</P>
<P>
The riots were also reported in the towns around London and
across the country, and five policemen were injuried in Bedford.
