<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Exchange Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
dropped sharply today due to nervousness before release of profit
returns of local blue chip BHP.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index tumbled 11 points to finish at 2,241.8
points.
</P>
<P>
BHP's share price shed 17 cents to 17.68 Australian dollars,
the lowest level in over seven months.
</P>
<P>
The Australian bourse was also weighed down by heavy selling
before large numbers of option rights to buy shares expire Friday.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index lost 13.4 points to close at 3,359.6
points, while the all resources index dropped 9.3 points to close
at 1,397.1 points.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 342.3 million shares, valued at
897.23 million Australian dollars (708.81 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the Sydney Futures Exchange, the June share price contract
index slid 17 points to finish at 2,236 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
