<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Gets Technical Aid From European Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has received 650,000 US
dollars worth of technical assistance from the European Union for
the Sri Lanka Standards Institution (SLSI) and the country's food
manufacturing sector, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The Leatherhead Food Research Association of England and the
National Standards Authority of Ireland (ITAI) have been appointed
consultants, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The assistance to the SLSI is designed to develop its technical
activities including laboratory accreditation and International
Standards Organization (ISO) certification scheme.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lanka food manufacturing sector would also benefit from
this project, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A seminar to stimulate interest in ISO quality management
systems in the food sector will be held as the first step under
this project, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
