<HEADLINE> 21 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Customs officers have
seized 21 kilograms of high grade heroin at the Hong Kong
International Airport Air Cargo Terminal.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Customs said here today that the batch of
drug was believed to be carried from the Chinese mainland to the
United States via Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is one of the largest catches of drugs seized
in Hong Kong this year and the street value of the drug is about
240 million HK dollars (30.96 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
He said that the seizure occurred last Tuesday, but for
investigation reason, the Customs office did not release the news.
</P>
<P>
Local media reported today that a Chinese-American was arrested
for his involvement in the drug trafficking and the case is under
further investigation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
