<HEADLINE> All Families in Hainan's Fenghuang Village Have Automobiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese village that until
recently depended on oxcarts and pedicabs as means of transport
has roared into the late 20th century.
</P>
<P>
Every single family in Fenghuang Village owns a car. While most
Chinese families can only dream of turning ox-power into horse
powered petrol engines, every family in the village has seen its
dreams come true.
</P>
<P>
The villagers, from near Sanya City in south China's Hainan
Province, have been able to take to the roads by making the best
use of their bestowed geological advantages.
</P>
<P>
The village, which has 780 families and the same number of
motor vehicles, scored a total income exceeding 10 million yuan
last year.
</P>
<P>
Ten years ago, however, the village only had oxcarts and
pedicabs as their major means of transport.
</P>
<P>
As the development pace quickened for Sanya City, farmers have
became rich, and all of them have built villas and bought vehicles.
</P>
<P>
In the average village family, each home has three people able
to drive, including many girls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
