<HEADLINE> 14 Passenger Planes Brought In China In First Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese airlines have acquired 14
foreign made passenger planes by purchasing or leasing in the
first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Eight of them are Boeing jets, and the other six are from
Europe's Airbus. They include one B777, five B737s, one B757, two
A340s, two A320s, and two A300.
</P>
<P>
Sources with China Aviation Supplies Corporation said ten of
the airplanes were purchased, and four have been leased.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern Airlines, Sichuan Airlines, and China Southern
Airlines are the first Chinese airline customers to have A340,
A320 and B777 in their fleets.
</P>
<P>
Other carriers to have had new planes include Air China,
Shandong Airlines, China Northwest Airlines, China Northern
Airlines, Xiamen Airlines and Xinhua Airlines.
</P>
<P>
China plans to increase its strength of civil airplanes this
year by 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
