<HEADLINE> India Takes Steps to Develop Tourism Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Indian Tourism Development
Corporation (ITDC) has taken steps to meet the target of 5 million
tourist arrivals by the end of the century, an ITDC official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The main task ahead of ITDC is to develop infrastructural
facilities at major tourist destinations to ease the burden on
gateway points, New Delhi and Bombay, he said.
</P>
<P>
Various tourist spots in India need to be provided with latest
telecommunication services and customs and immigration clearance
facilities. The spots also have to be uplinked with important
world centers through direct chartered flights to make them easily
accessible to foreign tourists, he added.  
</P>
