<HEADLINE> Share Prices Edge Up on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices edged up on the
Singapore market in quiet trading, as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials index gained 3.4 points to finish at 2,288.36 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 65.59 million units, valued
at 216.02 million Singapore dollars (about 154.3 million US
dollars). Falls led rises by 175 to 101, while 291 other stocks
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Amcol was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 10.22 million units. It was followed by the Singapore
Telecom which had 4.47 million of its shares traded. Amcol
warrant98 saw 3.04 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
GE Life was the biggest gainer of the day as it rose by one
Singapore dollar to close at 31.5 Singapore dollars. CMSPort was
next, picking up by 45 cents to 3.4 Hong Kong dollars. OUE and
the Sembawang Corporation gained 15 cents each to finish at 7.75
and seven Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, RDC topped the losers' list as it declined by
90 cents to 4.8 Singapore dollars. Amcol came in the second
place, falling by 76 cents to 3.1 Singapore dollars, while Amcol
warrant98 dropped by 68 cents to 2.12 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
