<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Names Rybkin to Head Consultative Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today appointed Ivan Rybkin, former speaker of the State Duma
(lower house of parliament), to head the Political Consultative
Council (PCC), the Presidential Press Service said.
</P>
<P>
The new public body was formed by Yeltsin to replace the Public
Chamber under the president in keeping with the recommendation of
several political parties and movements to promote interaction
between federal state organs and the public.
</P>
<P>
The president offered PCC membership first and foremost to the
political parties and movements represented in the Duma and also
the political parties and movements that failed to win seats in
the parliament during the latest elections, the press service said.
</P>
<P>
Observers here believe that by taking this step, Yeltsin is
seeking rapprochement with all political parties, including the
Communist Party, before the upcoming second round of the
presidential elections. 
</P>
