<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Boy with Three Kidneys Receives Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Surgeons at a hospital in east
China's Hangzhou city found that boy patient undergoing kidney
surgery had three kidneys, according to a local report.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year-old was sent to the Zhejiang Provincial People's
Hospital when he fell a two-meter height and suffered abdominal
problems, the "Beijing Evening News" reported.
</P>
<P>
Doctors carried out checks on the boy, and found that his right
kidney had undergone pathological changes. But, to their surprise,
they also found a third kidney besides the right kidney, half the
size of the normal one.
</P>
<P>
The doctors finally decided to remove the right kidney because
they believed the small kidney could also be functional, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The surgery was described as successful.  
</P>
