<HEADLINE> More Middle School Students Aspiring to CPC Membership (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All middle schools in China have Party organizations and
branches that care for the ideological trends of the students, and
help them define their thoughts and beliefs, an official with the
CYLC said.
</P>
<P>
Party courses are open to all middle schools and have become
one of the most favorite courses among students. In some middle
schools, part-time courses are run to assist those active in
joining the CPC to familiarize themselves with knowledge and
theories of Communism.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Zhiyuan, an official with the Chengdu City Education
Commission, said middle school students are young and immature. So
the major task of Party organizations in the schools is to help
them further nurture and solidify their beliefs.
</P>
<P>
"Only a minority of middle school applicants qualify for the
strict examinations," Zheng said. "Not everyone is so much
qualified as Gaisang Dawa."
</P>
<P>
Gaisang Dawa comes from a herdsman family of Maizhokunggar
County, Tibet Autonomous Region. He said his family now have their
own farmland, TV set, Hi-fi recorders and other modern household
appliances.
</P>
<P>
"Last year we built a large house. My Grandma, a poor serf
in feudalistic Tibet, is happily enjoying her twilight years in
the building," Gaisang said, adding "all these improvements are
owed to the Communist Party."
</P>
<P>
An eye-witness to the great changes that have taken place in
his hometown and his family, the student Party member strongly
defend the CPC against reproach over corruption and abuse of power.
</P>
<P>
He said corruption did come up within the Party but they are
single and rare cases. The nationwide campaign to crack down on
corrupt activities in its ranks, including high-ranking officials,
is a strong indication of CPC's determination to stamp out
corruption.
</P>
<P>
"The CPC is an organization that dedicates itself to the welfare
of the broad masses and deserves my trust," Gaisang Dawa said, "I
will devote all my life to the cause of Communism."  
</P>
</TEXT>
