<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Assist Cambodia in Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
offer technical assistance to Cambodia in the 1997 local elections
and the 1998 general elections, a visiting delegation of EU
ambassadors announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The EU ambassadors made the announcement at a press conference
at the end of their four-day visit to Cambodia, the first of its
kind since the establishment of the royal government of Cambodia
in 1993.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the ambassadors discussed with Cambodian
officials matters related to the local elections in 1997 and the
general elections in 1998.
</P>
<P>
They said the Cambodian side was interested in having
international cooperation in the elections.
</P>
<P>
The ambassadors, who had toured several Cambodian provinces,
noted that they were happy to see the achievements made by the
Cambodian government in the last two years in utilizing EU
humanitarian aid to improve drinking water supply and education
for the rural people.
</P>
<P>
They were also pleased to find that the humanitarian help has
brought confidence to the Cambodian people in their development.
</P>
<P>
The EU will provide funds to Cambodia for environmental
protection and help the country draw up a long-term environmental
protection plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
