<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Villagers Scale New Heights on the Wings of Kites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Dongtun Village in north
China's Shageda Township has a kite making history spanning over
50 years. It is known as the "Kite Village" in Daming County in
Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Every family in the village are traditionally good at making
kites. The difference between the past and present is that the
villagers used to make kites just for self entertainment, or the
fun of their children now they are making big money from them.
</P>
<P>
An average family can make 4,000 or 5,000 kites a year in their
spare, and some can even make more than ten thousand.
</P>
<P>
Some neighboring villages are cashing in on the success of
Dongtun by starting themselves to make and sell kites, but Dongtun
has become the main distribution center of kites. Their kites are
sold in more than 20 cities in China, including Beijing, Tianjin,
Xi'an and Guangzhou. Last year, Dongtun Village sold over 400,000
kites around the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
