<HEADLINE> Wenzhou Leads Zhejiang Province in Mobile Phones Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Wenzhou, a coastal city in east
China's Zhejiang Province, leads the province in mobile phone
subscribers with more than 60,000, the People's Post and
Telecommunications Journal reported.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period this year, the city added 24,392
mobile phone users, bringing the total to 60,548, more than 7,800
of which subscribed to GSM.
</P>
<P>
During recent years, the city's mobile communication has
witnessed a speedy development, with mobile phone owners rising
from 727 in 1992, and to 36,156 in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
