<HEADLINE> Tianjin's Export-oriented Agriculture Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin had more than 2,400
foreign-funded enterprises involved in agriculture by the end of
last year, with total contractual investment worth 3.5 billion US
dollars, of which 2.2 billion US dollars were from foreign
investment.
</P>
<P>
The munipality's rural industrial enterprises produced 11.5
billion yuan worth of exports last year, an increase of 25 percent
over the previous year, in everything from machinery, garments,
carpets, and handicrafts to daily-use articles exported to over 80
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
A study has shown that Tianjin imported 58 pieces of advanced
technology and equipment and more than 100 fine livestock breeds
over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
At present, it has offered 100 projects in opening up barren
mountainsides, wasteland and beaches, and in tourism looking for
cooperation with investors from other parts of China and
overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
