<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ATM Network to Cover Guangdong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, one of China's
booming coastal economic areas, will complete a pilot ATM
(asynchronous transport model) network to cover nine cities by the
end of 1997, according to Guangdong-Hong Kong Information Daily.
</P>
<P>
On basis of this advanced network, the province will build a
high-speed information web in Pearl River Delta in 2010, said Cui
Xun, director of Guangdong Provincial Posts and Telecommunications
Administration, at an international technical symposium in
Guangzhou, the province capital.
</P>
<P>
The ATM network will consist of a Guangzhou-based broad-band
multimedia service center, ATM accesses in Shenzhen, Zhuhai,
Foshan and other cities in the delta, and some ATM switching
systems in neighboring cities.
</P>
<P>
Research and development of broad-band telecom products will
further accelerate in the province, Cui said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
