<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 440 Million Yuan Aid Needy College Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The central government has
allocated 440 million yuan to aid financially-dependent university
students since 1994.
</P>
<P>
According to today's People's Daily, a recent survey issued by
the State Education Committee (SEC) showed that approximately
293,000 students are enrolled in the 34 colleges and universities
directly under the SEC.
</P>
<P>
About 49,700 students, or 17 percent of the total, have
financial difficulties, and 18,600 of them live in poverty, the
survey showed.
</P>
<P>
A near-complete financial aid system has been formed in
institutions of higher-learning to aid poor students by granting
loans, stipends and scholarship, or reducing or remitting the
tuition fees for some students who are in extreme financial
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, 9.44-million-yuan loans were issued to aid 20,458
college students; 22.17-million-yuan work-study funds went to
60,375; and 17,77-million-yuan stipends went to 57,230.
</P>
<P>
Reduced or remitted tuition fees for another 3,267 students
totalled 1.58 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, about 276,212 outstanding college students were
awarded various kinds of scholarships totaling 76,38 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to the SEC, more flexible policies are expected to be
implemented in the country's institutions of higher learning over
the next two years to assist financially-dependent but outstanding
students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
