<HEADLINE> Ford to Set Up Joint Automobile Development Laboratory in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The US's Ford Motor Company will
join Shanghai Jiaotong University to create an automobile
development laboratory in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Ford will provide one million US dollars-worth of aid for the
laboratory, which will carry out research work in the fields of
computer aided design (CAD), computer aided engineering (CAE),
computer aided manufacturing (CAM), and product information
management (PIM).
</P>
<P>
The laboratory will be the first of its kind in Asia.  
</P>
