<HEADLINE> Chin, Portugal Sign Two Summaries Concerning Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MACAO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- China and Portugal signed another
two summaries of talks here today on Macao's entry into two
international bodies.
</P>
<P>
The summaries were signed at the 26th session of the
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group (JLG), which closed today. The
summaries were on Macao's entry into an international labor
supervision body and an international body of post workers of the
Portuguese-speaking nations.
</P>
<P>
Previously, the two sides signed a summary on the air
transportation agreements between Macao and the Republic of Korea,
Denmark, Norway and Sweden on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Guo Jiading, chief representative of the Chinese team of the
Sino-Portuguese JLG, told reporters that a number of important
issues were also discussed today between the Chinese side and the
Portuguese side at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Those issues include the handover of archives and
government-owned assets, financial reserves, agreements on
monopolized operation of some industries, the establishment of a
Portuguese language school after 1999, the pension of civil
servants and the listing of some Macao scenic sites into United
Nations historic relics, Guo said.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Santana Carlos, chief representative of the Portuguese
team of the Sino-Portuguese JLG, stressed today's meeting was
convened in a friendly and frankly atmosphere and certain progress
has been achieved.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
