<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First High-level Economic Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOLMUD, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Three years of effort have gone
into putting together the Kunlun Economic Development Zone in
Golmud, in northwest China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
This is China's first economic development zone built on a
plateau, in this case the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, a move that is
meant to exploit the resources of the Qaidam Basin.
</P>
<P>
With 280,000 square kilometers of space, the zone has completed
a project to provide 6,000 tons of water daily, a 110-kv power
project, a heat supply project for 120,000 square meters, and a
300-line program-controlled telephone project.
</P>
<P>
It has also built 4,430 sq m of office space and 4,800 sq m of
commercial residential space.
</P>
<P>
With 560 million yuan in contractual funds, the zone has
introduced 164 development projects and registered 160
enterprises, which invested 70 million yuan in basic construction.
</P>
<P>
In order to develop the resources of the Qaidam Basin, local
authorities will contact more domestic and overseas businesspeople
to encourage them to put a larger amount of investment into the
zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
