<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times
</P>
<P>
-- Indian Foreign Secretary Salman Haider has been given a
year-long extension in service starting from July 1 this year. He
was to have retired on June 30.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India
</P>
<P>
-- The Directorate of Enforcement (DOE) on Wednesday
transferred 130 middle and senior level officers to weed out
vested interests in the DOE.
</P>
<P>
The Statesman
</P>
<P>
-- Former prime minister P.V. Narasimha Rao completed Russian
arms deal at a hurried pace.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Times
</P>
<P>
-- Leading foreign institutional investors have been
accumulating shares of Industrial Development Bank of India on a
large scale through off-market deals.  
</P>
