<HEADLINE> WFP Provides Relief Food To Somali Villagers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Programme (WFP)
has distributed 60 tons of ungently-needed relief food to 11,000
villagers in the Middle Juba Valley districts in south-western
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The move is to prevent further population movements towards
the Kenya border due to hunger and insecurity, WFP said in a
press statement issued here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Over the last two months, significant numbers of people from
the Juba Valley and the Bay/Nakool regions have migrated to
Kismayo and to the Kenyan border because of insecurity and food
shortages," the WFP statement said.
</P>
<P>
"In mid-may, some 600 Somali refugees arrived in Dadaab camp
in Kenya. An estimated 1,400 newly displaced people are
currently poised near the border," the WFP added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
