<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Makes Efforts to Develop Gold Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province, one
of the major gold production bases in the country, is expected to
turn out 10 tons of gold in the next five years, "China Gold News"
has reported.
</P>
<P>
The State Bureau of Gold Administration earlier reported that
China turned out 105 tons of gold last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the blueprint, Jiangxi Province plans to produce
another 10 tons of gold by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
In the coming years, the province will focus on the technical
retooling of the existing gold mines along the much-publicized
Beijing-Kowloon Railway, and the development of gold resources in
the old gold mining areas, the newspaper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
