<HEADLINE> Public Phones Seen Everywhere in Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Public phone booths can be seen
everywhere in this scenic city in east China's Zhejiang Province,
and are a welcome convenience for both travelers and local residents.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou, reputed one of the most beautiful cities in the
country, now has nearly 8,000 public phones in the city, or an
average of five phones for each 1,000 local people -- close to the
standard of six phones per thousand residents reported in
developed nations.
</P>
<P>
About 10 million travelers visit the city annually over recent
years. In the past, people were often seen waiting in line to make
calls from the public phones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
