<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats Mexico in Friendly Match of Olympians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The United States Olympic
soccer team defeated their Mexican counterparts 1-0 in an
exhibition match Wednesday night at the St. Louis Soccer Park in
Fenton, United States.
</P>
<P>
Jovan Kirovski scored on a penalty kick at the 49th minute
past Mexican goalie Alexandro Alvarez.
</P>
<P>
Alvarez pulled down Miles Joseph just to the right of the
Mexican goal and referee Rich Grady called for a penalty kick.
</P>
<P>
Kirovski scored past Alvarez, who kept Mexico in the game
by making six saves, into the lower left corner.
</P>
<P>
The hosting squad dominated the match throughout and the
Mexican offence hardly tested U.S. goalie Kasey Keller, who had
to make only two saves.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6,200 spectators attended the friendly match.
</P>
</TEXT>
