<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Gets Grant From France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Kenya has got a grant of 400
million Kenya Shillings (about 7 million U.S. Dollars) for water
supply in Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
The agreement for the grant signed by Kenya Finance Minister
Musalia Mudavadi and French Ambassador to Kenya Jacques Depaigne
in Nairobi on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the grant will be used in leakage
control operations and for the improvement of distribution of
water in Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
It will also benefit the Directorate of Civil Aviation, Kenya
Railways and Survey of Kenya. 
</P>
</TEXT>
