<DOCNO> XIE19960627.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines to Tighten Supervision Over Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MANILA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine central bank plans
to tighten its hold on the banking system through the issuance of
new guidelines in the selection of bank directors.
</P>
<P>
The Business Daily reported here today that the central bank
is seeking authority for the Monetary Board (MB) to prescribe a
set of minimum standards for bank directors and officers.
</P>
<P>
These norms will be included among the amendments to the
general banking act to be presented to the congress.
</P>
<P>
Once it is given a legislative mandate to do so, MB plans to
subject bank directors to a "fit and proper" examination.
</P>
<P>
Although the central bank acknowledges the right of banks'
stock-holders to elect its directors, it wants to have a say in
screening these people.
</P>
<P>
This is to ensure that the operations of all local banks will
be handled by competent people, and thus, pave the way for an even
healthier banking environment.
</P>
<P>
In the past, some banks, particularly small rural banks,
suffered financial losses due to mishandling by incompetent
directors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960627.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Fund Welcomed in Northeast China Industry Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China will use more
foreign capital in the next five years to upgrade its industrial
performance.
</P>
<P>
With a total area of 1.24 million sq km and a population of 120
million, northeast China is one of the country's major chemical
and energy industry bases. The bulk of foreign investment that is
here is attracted mainly by the region's sound industrial base and
abundant resources.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Province will use 10 billion US dollars during the
Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) to reform its state-owned
petrochemical, metallurgical, electronic and machinery industries,
according to the plan.
</P>
<P>
The province will allow two-thirds of its over 1,200 major and
medium-sized industrial enterprises to receive foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Jilin Province plans to inject nearly five billion US dollars,
40 percent of which are planned for overseas investment, for the
technical renovation of its industrial enterprises. It will use
more than four billion US dollars of foreign investment during the
five-year period that ends in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The province will see 90 percent of its industrial enterprises
regraded through overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang Province in northeast China plans to use 2.5
billion US dollars over the next five years. Most of the funds
will be used to introduce advanced technology and equipment to
out-dated industrial enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The three provinces had used a total of 22.65 billion US
dollars by the end of last year. Businessmen from more than 60
countries and regions have invested in the region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
