<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Publishes First History Book </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan's first book on its
own history has come off the press today.
</P>
<P>
The four-volume work, Kazakhstan History, is jointly compiled
by researchers from Kazakhstan's Archeological Research Institute
and History and Ethnological Research Institute. It is the first
book that describes the country's history in an objective and
all-round way.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on its publication, Kazakh First Deputy Prime
Minister Nigmatzhan Isingarin said the book will definitely help
strengthen national harmony and promote education in patriotism
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Before Kazakhstan's independence from the former Soviet Union
in 1991, most Kazakhs were taught at schools history of the Soviet
Union and Russia, and knew little about Kazakhstan's own history.
</P>
