<HEADLINE> River Plate Wins Libertadores Cup Soccer Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's River Plate
defeated Colombia's America de Cali 2-0 in the second leg of the
final to wrest the title of the Libertadores Cup soccer
tournament with a 2-1 aggregate at the River Plate stadium here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hernan Crespo of River Plate scored the opening goal in the 6th
minute of the game and his teammate Hernan Crespo added another
goal in the 59th minute.
</P>
<P>
The match drew more than 75,000 spectators at the stadium.
</P>
