<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Makes Further Step to Win Election Runoff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Tuesday ordered the president-controlled public committee to be
changed into a political consultative committee, Interfax and
Itar-Tass news agencies reported today.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the president issued the order at the
suggestion of several political parties and organizations and he
invited Ivan Rybkin, the former chairman of the State Duma, to
head the new body.
</P>
<P>
The body's main functions are to discuss the draft plans of the
president and the government on political, economic, social issues
and help them draft bills on political and economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin won 33.77 percent of votes in the first round of
presidential elections on June 16, a narrow lead of 3 percent
ahead of his communist challenger Gennady Zyuganov.
</P>
<P>
To boost his chances of winning the run-off election on July 3,
Yeltsin sacked Defense Minister Pavel Grachev and seven other
generals recently. The reform of the public committee is widely
seen as another of his series of moves toward his goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
