<HEADLINE> Fire Erupts in US Treasury Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A fire broke out in the U.S.
Treasury Building Wednesday afternoon, forcing hundreds of
government workers to evacuate from the 19th building next to the
White House, but there were no immediate reports of injuries.
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said the blaze erupted on the roof of the
125-year-old structure. Heavy smoke filled the fifth floor and
basement of the building.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire was not known. But the building was under
renovation and officials of the Treasury's secret service said it
appeared that some material they were using or the roof caught
fire.
</P>
<P>
The fire department evacuated hundreds of people from the
structure at about 4:30 p.m. and closed off surrounding streets to
traffic.
</P>
<P>
The building has mostly offices including the office of
Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin on the third floor. 
</P>
