<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Circular Demands Tax Rebates to Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The State Administration of
Taxation has issued an emergent circular telling tax departments
nationwide that they should get tax rebates to exporters
efficiently and with speed.
</P>
<P>
"While enhancing the collection of taxes and improving the
management of tax rebates for exports, the payment of tax rebates
set by state standards should be accelerated," the circular said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that delivery of tax rebates has slowed down
since the start of this year. The amount of tax rebates during the
first four months was 15.63 billion yuan (about 1.8 billion US
dollars), down 42 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Exporters of machinery, electronics products, and silk and
those who have never cheated on their taxes should have priority
in getting tax rebates, the circular said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that payment of tax rebates should also be tilted in
favor of credit-worthy exporting enterprises, especially large
ones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
