<HEADLINE> Dragon Cards Promoted in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Construction Bank of China,
one of China's four state commercial banks, has launched a
campaign to widely promote Dragon Cards in large enterprises in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement between the local branch of the bank
and the Shanghai Volkswagen Auto Co. Ltd, employees with the
car-maker will settle all accounts with the credit cards issued by
the bank to the company.
</P>
<P>
The bank has introduced Dragon Cards into the Baoshan Iron and
Steel Corporation to quicken capital flow.
</P>
<P>
An official with the bank said that it is expected to
popularize Dragon Cards in more large enterprises in Shanghai in
the near future.
</P>
<P>
The bank has issued 143,000 Dragon Cards in the Shanghai region
and put 180 ATMs into operation. In the first five months of this
year, transactions valued at 1.328 billion yuan were conducted
using the cards. 
</P>
