<HEADLINE> New Shipping Lines For Chinese Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A new cargo container shipping
line has been opened between the east China port of Xiamen and the
Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
There are two scheduled sailings on the route each month.
</P>
<P>
It is the second international line opened this year by the
port in Fujian Province, China Transport News reported. The first
was to the United States, opened in March.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen now has four international container shipping
lines. The other two are to Japan and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The paper also reported that Lianyungang, another east China
port, is to open a new container shipping line to the two ports of
Pusan and Mason in the Republic of Korea at the beginning of next
month. 
</P>
