<HEADLINE> Serb Forces Have Implemented Dayton Agreement: Serb Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Bosnian Serb forces have fully
carried out all their obligations under the Dayton agreement and
will continue to do so, their Chief of Staff Man Milovanovich told
reporters today.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnian Serb forces have been reformed as required by last
November's Dayton peace accord which ended the nearly four-year
war in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The forces have also reduced their weapons in accordance with
the disarmament accord reached earlier this month in Florence,
Italy.
</P>
<P>
But, said Milovanovich, the question of defense must not be
neglected, because genuine peace depends on power, technology,
training and the motivation of the soldiers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
