<HEADLINE> Private Entrepreneur in Zhejiang Finances University Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Li Huiliang, a private
entrepreneur in east China's Zhejiang Province, has donated ten
million yuan (about 1.2 million US dollars) to finance the
first-phase of construction for an education building at Jinhua
University.
</P>
<P>
When the first phase is completed, the building will have a
floor space of 16,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Li, 46, now serves as chairman of the the Aotuokang
Pharmaceutical Group in Zhejiang. After resigning as a government
office worker in 1992, he went to Shanghai, the largest city in
China, and set up a real estate company.
</P>
<P>
Later, he built a number of companies in Zhejiang, including an
80-million yuan hydroelectric power station in Taizhou City.
</P>
<P>
He also spent 35.7 million yuan to buy 36 percent of the stock
of the Aotuokang Pharmaceutical Company.
</P>
<P>
Li, a farmer's son, could not afford to study in a university.
</P>
<P>
"I think my life value lies in doing good things for society,"
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
