<HEADLINE> Perry to Visit American Troops in Balkans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Defense Secretary William
Perry will travel to Europe next week to visit American troops in
Bosnia and hold security talks with his European counterparts, the
Pentagon said today.
</P>
<P>
Perry, who is departing Saturday, will first visit U.S. Navy
ships in the Mediterranean Sunday and then make stops in Italy,
Hungary, Bosnia and Slovenia, a senior U.S. Defense Department
official told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The Pentagon chief will visit American troops based in Taszar,
Hungary, on July 2. The American troops there are supporting the
18,000-strong U.S. peace implementation force in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The next day, Perry will tour Bosnia with stops in Sarajevo,
Banja Luka and Mostar.
</P>
<P>
After a brief visit to Slovenia, Perry will spend the July 4
Independence Day holiday with American troops based near the
northern Bosnian city of Tuzla, the official said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Perry might also go to Saudi Arabia to visit
U.S. forces, he said. Nineteen American servicemen were killed and
more than 200 injured in a terrorist attack at a U.S. military
housing area near Dhahran, Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
