<HEADLINE> Fire Breaks Out in US Treasury Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A fire broke out in the U.S.
Treasury Building this afternoon, forcing hundreds of people to
evacuate, but no one was reported injured.
</P>
<P>
Heavy smoke could be seen from the fifth floor and the basement
of the building, which is next to the White House on Pennsylvania
Avenue.
</P>
<P>
Restoration work is under way on the building. Treasury
security officials said it appeared that some material they were
using or the roof caught fire.
</P>
<P>
The Washington, D.C. fire department evacuated hundreds of
people from the building and closed off surrounding streets to
traffic. 
