<HEADLINE> S. Africa Releases Details on New Salary System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- South African Justice
Minister Dullar Omar today released the new salary structures for
state prosecutors, advocates, legal administration officers and
members of the state attorney's office.
</P>
<P>
In terms of the new grading system, state advocates received
the highest average percentage increase of 14.58 percent, with
increases ranging from 9 percent to 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors received increases ranging from 10 to 24 percent,
with an average increase of 13.78 percent.
</P>
<P>
Legal administration officers received increases of between 9
and 24 percent, with an average of 13.83 percent, while members
of the state attorney's office received an average increase of
13.70 percent, with increases ranging from 9 to 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Pretoria, Omar said all allowances
had been abolished and incorporated into the new salary.
</P>
<P>
Omar said the public service and administration department
forwarded the new grading system to the justice department last
week.
</P>
<P>
The new salary structure for magistrates had also been
finalised after consultation with Minister of Finance Trevor
Manuel, said Omar. enditem

